The paper focuses on social signal processing and the use of nonverbal behavior to detect emergent leaders in small groups. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to extract features from visual data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for prediction, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of facial action units, which suggests that it may belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of online prediction, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
